! Manso enumerates and develops at some length the following sources of the royal revenue of Theodoric . 
A domain , either by succession to that of Odoacer , or a part of the third of the lands was reserved for the royal patrimony . 
Regalia , including mines , unclaimed estates , treasure trove , and confiscations . 
Aurarium , like the Chrysargyrum , a tax on certain branches of trade . 
Siliquaticum , a small tax on the sale of all kinds of commodities . 
