But the reproach of cruelty , so repugnant even to her softer vices , has left an indelible stain on the memory of Theodora . 
Her numerous spies observed , and zealously reported , every action , or word , or look , injurious to their royal mistress . 
The senator or bishop , whose death or exile Theodora had pronounced , was delivered to a trusty messenger , and his diligence was quickened by a menace from her own mouth . 
If you fail in the execution of my commands , I swear by Him who liveth forever , that your skin shall be flayed from your body . 
Darkness is propitious to cruelty , but it is likewise favorable to calumny and fiction . 
A more jocular whipping was inflicted on Saturninus , for presuming to say that his wife , a favorite of the empress , had not been found . 
Per viventem in saecula excoriari te faciam . 
If the creed of Theodora had not been tainted with heresy , her exemplary devotion might have atoned , in the opinion of her contemporaries , for pride , avarice , and cruelty . 
The prudence of Theodora is celebrated by Justinian himself and his laws are attributed to the sage counsels of his most reverend wife whom he had received as the gift of the Deity . 
Her courage was displayed amidst the tumult of the people and the terrors of the court . 
The wishes and prayers of Theodora could never obtain the blessing of a lawful son , and she buried an infant daughter , the sole offspring of her marriage . 
Perhaps her health had been impaired by the licentiousness of her youth but it was always delicate , and she was directed by her physicians to use the Pythian warm baths . 
