But the consternation of the soldiers of the tower , who either fled or deserted , disappointed his hopes , and betrayed his person into the most imminent danger . 
The fate of Italy depended on his life and the deserters pointed to the conspicuous horse a bay , with a white face , which he rode on that memorable day . 
Aim at the bay horse , was the universal cry . 
Every bow was bent , every javelin was directed , against that fatal object , and the command was repeated and obeyed by thousands who were ignorant of its real motive . 
