They reigned over the north but they confessed the vanity of conquest , by their faithful attachment to the mountain of their fathers . 
One of the successors of Bertezena was tempted by the luxury and superstition of China but his design of building cities and temples was defeated by the simple wisdom of a Barbarian counsellor . 
The Turks , he said , are not equal in number to one hundredth part of the inhabitants of China . 
If we balance their power , and elude their armies , it is because we wander without any fixed habitations in the exercise of war and hunting . 
Are we strong ? we advance and conquer are we feeble ? we retire and are concealed . 
