After they had been purified with fire and incense , according to a rite still practised under the sons of Zingis , they were introduced to the presence of Disabul . 
In a valley of the Golden Mountain , they found the great khan in his tent , seated in a chair with wheels , to which a horse might be occasionally harnessed . 
You see my ten fingers , said the great khan , and he applied them to his mouth . 
You Romans speak with as many tongues , but they are tongues of deceit and perjury . 
To me you hold one language , to my subjects another and the nations are successively deluded by your perfidious eloquence . 
You precipitate your allies into war and danger , you enjoy their labors , and you neglect your benefactors . 
Hasten your return , inform your master that a Turk is incapable of uttering or forgiving falsehood , and that he shall speedily meet the punishment which he deserves . 
While he solicits my friendship with flattering and hollow words , he is sunk to a confederate of my fugitive Varchonites . 
