A soldier trained in the school of Belisarius , Paul of Cilicia , retired with four hundred men to the mole of Hadrian . 
They repelled the Goths but they felt the approach of famine and their aversion to the taste of horse flesh confirmed their resolution to risk the event of a desperate and decisive sally . 
Whilst he amused the eyes of the multitude , four hundred vessels were prepared for the embarkation of his troops . 
