M. Justinian was deaf to the voice of peace but he neglected the prosecution of war and the indolence of his temper disappointed , in some degree , the obstinacy of his passions . 
In the choice of the generals , caprice , as well as judgment , was shown . 
In the place of Liberius , the conspirator Artaban was raised from a prison to military honors in the pious presumption , that gratitude would animate his valor and fortify his allegiance . 
The Romans advanced to Sardica an army of Sclavonians fled before their march but within two days of their final departure , the designs of Germanus were terminated by his malady and death . 
Yet the impulse which he had given to the Italian war still continued to act with energy and effect . 
