Dog , wilt thou strike thy Lord ? was the more characteristic exclamation of the Gothic youth . 
As soon as Narses had paid his devotions to the Author of victory , and the blessed Virgin , his peculiar patroness , he praised , rewarded , and dismissed the Lombards . 
But the deliverance of Rome was the last calamity of the Roman people . 
The Barbarian allies of Narses too frequently confounded the privileges of peace and war . 
The fate of the senate suggests an awful lesson of the vicissitude of human affairs . 
