Besides the agreement of the parties , the essence of every rational contract , the Roman marriage required the previous approbation of the parents . 
A father might be forced by some recent laws to supply the wants of a mature daughter but even his insanity was not gradually allowed to supersede the necessity of his consent . 
The causes of the dissolution of matrimony have varied among the Romans but the most solemn sacrament , the confarreation itself , might always be done away by rites of a contrary tendency . 
