The freedom of love and marriage was restrained among the Romans by natural and civil impediments . 
An instinct , almost innate and universal , appears to prohibit the incestuous commerce of parents and children in the infinite series of ascending and descending generations . 
Concerning the oblique and collateral branches , nature is indifferent , reason mute , and custom various and arbitrary . 
