The general duties of mankind are imposed by their public and private relations but their specific obligations to each other can only be the effect of , . 
an injury and when these obligations are ratified by law , the interested party may compel the performance by a judicial action . 
On this principle , the civilians of every country have erected a similar jurisprudence , the fair conclusion of universal reason and justice . 
