The destruction of a mighty kingdom established the fame of Alboin . 
But his ambition was yet unsatisfied and the conqueror of the Gepidae turned his eyes from the Danube to the richer banks of the Po , and the Tyber . 
No sooner had he erected his standard , than the native strength of the Lombard was multiplied by the adventurous youth of Germany and Scythia . 
Of the Saxons , the old allies of the Lombards , twenty thousand warriors , with their wives and children , accepted the invitation of Alboin . 
Their bravery contributed to his success but the accession or the absence of their numbers was not sensibly felt in the magnitude of his host . 
