It is devoutly believed by the Catholics , and admitted by Casaubon , Grotius , and Isaac Vossius , among the Protestant critics . 
But this Hebrew Gospel of St . 
Matthew is most unaccountably lost and we may accuse the diligence or fidelity of the primitive churches , who have preferred the unauthorized version of some nameless Greek . 
Erasmus and his followers , who respect our Greek text as the original Gospel , deprive themselves of the evidence which declares it to be the work of an apostle . 
