Justinian was neither steady nor consistent in the nice process of fixing his volatile opinions and those of his subjects . 
A bishop of Treves , secure beyond the limits of his power , addressed the monarch of the East in the language of authority and affection . 
Most gracious Justinian , remember your baptism and your creed . 
