This name , unknown till the xth century , appears to be of Syriac origin . 
The Syriac , which the natives revere as the primitive language , was divided into three dialects . 
The Aramoean , as it was refined at Edessa and the cities of Mesopotamia . 
The Palestine , which was used in Jerusalem , Damascus , and the rest of Syria . 
