Hereafter I shall relate his valiant , but unsuccessful , efforts to resist the progress of the Turks . 
Strong in the contempt of their sovereign and their own esteem , two generals , at the head of the European and Asiatic legions , assumed the purple at Adrianople and Nice . 
While Botaniates advanced with cautious and dilatory steps , his active competitor stood in arms before the gates of Constantinople . 
This change of the public opinion was favorable to Botaniates , who at length , with an army of Turks , approached the shores of Chalcedon . 
